## Reporting a Vulnerability

If you discover a security vulnerability, please report it responsibly:

**Contact:** [security email or reporting URL]
**Response time:** We aim to acknowledge reports within [48 hours / 5 business days].

**Please include:**
- Description of the vulnerability
- Steps to reproduce
- Impact assessment (what could an attacker do?)
- Any suggested fix (optional)

**Please do NOT:**
- Open a public GitHub issue for security vulnerabilities
- Exploit the vulnerability beyond what is needed to demonstrate it
- Access or modify other users' data

## Safe Harbor

We consider security research conducted in good faith to be authorized activity. We will not pursue legal action against researchers who:

- Make a good faith effort to avoid privacy violations and service disruptions
- Report vulnerabilities to us before disclosing publicly
- Allow reasonable time for remediation before disclosure

## Security Update Process

Security patches are released as [hotfix releases / part of regular release cycle].
Critical vulnerabilities are patched within [24 hours / 72 hours] of confirmation.

Users are notified of security updates via [GitHub releases / email / in-app notification].
